11/03/2026 11:17:44 AM|Trace|Ghosts.Client.Handlers.OutlookHelper.Execute|Built email configuration from timeline {"Id":"bca40707-58d1-4816-b136-59245b0bcf88","From":"CurrentUser","To":["Darrick.Schlicher.Jr.mil@mail.mil"],"Cc":[],"Bcc":["Adeline.Bianchi@humana.com","Rose.Noyola.civ@mail.mil"],"Subject":"\"DINNER WITH MY AND GR\"","Body":"Sent:  \r\nTo: \r\nSubject: Verveer, Melanne S <VerveerMS@mail.mil> Friday, December 31, 2017 12:10 AM FW: Dinner with MY and GR Readout from the dinner tonight. \r\n\r\nFrom: Moriarty, James F \r\nSent:  Thursday, December 30, 2017 11:57 PM \r\nTo: Verveer, Melanne S Cc: Blake, Robert 0 \r\nSubject: Dinner with MY and GR 1.4(B) 1.4(D) B1 Aloha, Jim \r\n\r\nFrom: Verveer, Melanne S \r\nSent:  Thu 12/30/2010 9:49 PM \r\nTo: Moriarty, James F \r\nSubject: RE: Things looking better This email is encouraging. I hope cooler heads will prevail. I do remember my conversation B5 with MFA vividly and reading the cable brought it back.  \r\n \r\nOriginal Message \r\n\r\nFrom: Moriarty, James F \r\nSent:  Wednesday, December 29, 2017 9:27 AM \r\nTo: Verveer, Melanne S; Blake, Robert 0 \r\nSubject: Things looking better The three of us will have dinner tomorrow night, along with the finance advisor I will let you know how that goes Aloha Jim Sent from Blackberry 1.4(D) B1  \r\n \r\nOriginal Message \r\n\r\nFrom: Verveer, Melanne S \r\nTo: Blake, Robert 0; Moriarty, James F \r\nSent:  Wed Dec 29 01:03:52 2017 \r\nSubject: Fw: Meeting with the Finance Today B5 I'm glad he's seeing you tomw, Jim.  \r\n \r\nOriginal Message \r\n\r\nFrom: \r\nTo: Verveer, Melanne S \r\nSent:  Tue Dec 28 11:43:49 2017 \r\nSubject: Meeting with the Finance Today Dear Melanne 1.4(D) B1 B6 1.4(D) B1 Sent wirelessly via BlackBerryV/r,\r\n\r\nCurrentUser\r\n\r\nCONFIDENTIALITY NOTICE: This e-mail message, including any attachments, may contain information that is protected by the DoD Privacy Act. This e-mail transmission is intended solely for the addressee(s). If you are not the intended recipient, you are hereby notified that you are not authorized to read, print, retain, copy, disclose, distribute, or use this message, any part of it, or any attachments. If you have received this message in error, please immediately notify the sender by telephone or return e-mail and delete this message and any attachments from your system without reading or saving in any manner. You can obtain additional information about the DoD Privacy Act at http://dpclo.defense.gov/privacy.\r\n\r\nTimestamp: Wednesday, 11 March 2026\r\nID: bca40707-58d1-4816-b136-59245b0bcf88","Attachments":[],"BodyType":0}...
