11/03/2026 11:28:32 AM|Trace|Ghosts.Client.Handlers.OutlookHelper.Execute|Built email configuration from timeline {"Id":"2ae9bfaf-d0a4-4f92-8cdd-9e1f5d2c3c59","From":"CurrentUser","To":["Kathey.Machen@baesystems.com","Nana.Pham.mil@mail.mil","Raven.Torgersen.civ@mail.mil"],"Cc":["Claude.Rencher@lockheedmartin.com","Celia.l.Axel@humana.com"],"Bcc":["Marci.R.Fitzmaurice@baesystems.com","Candelaria.Flippen@boeing.com"],"Subject":"\"SECRETARY IN TRIPOLI\"","Body":"From: Mille, Brooke A <BAMille@mail.mil� \r\nSent:  Friday, October 21, 2011 5:17 AM \r\nTo: \r\nSubject: Fw:in Tripoli \r\n\r\nFrom: Cretz, Gene A \r\nSent:  Friday, October 21, 2011 04:50 AM \r\nTo: Mille, Brooke A  \r\n \r\nSubject:In Tripoli T hanks for the kind words. I think the Secretary's visit here was picture perfect given the chaos we labor under in Libya.Thewas great and her efforts will I think help us move forward on our project to help the war-wounded. On a lighter note, I will never be lonely here after thewas kind enough to give my personal contact information to all 120,000 students at the university during her stirring dialogue with them. It has been quite a week ;I don't think I can take any more excitement. All the best, Gene. \r\n\r\nFrom: Mille, Brooke A \r\nSent:  Sunday, October 16, 2011 2:36 PM \r\nTo: Cretz, Gene A  \r\nSubject RE: contact Thanks so much Gene - you have been a terrific partner in a hard circumstance. I think we will move forward with seeking to have Chris become charge in January and then nominate him subsequently so he can begin serving. B6 cdm \r\n\r\nFrom: Cretz, Gene A \r\nSent:  Friday, October 14, 2011 1:36 PM To Mille, Brooke A \r\nSubject: contact Hi Cheryl: hope this finds you well. I know that Jeff has been in touch with you regarding the switch between myself and Chris Stevens. I just wanted you to know that I am prepared to do whatever you and thethink is best. I met with Pat Kennedy and Bill Burns before I left and told them please rest assured that I consider myself extremely fortunate to B6 have had the opportunity to work closely with/for theduring the past 8 months. I consider the Secretary's visit to Tripoli this coming week to be the high point of my 30 year career. Warm regards, Gene. PERSONAL This email is  \r\n \r\nUNCLASSIFIED. ARMY - PRODUCED TO HOUSE SELECT  COMM.  \r\nSUBJECT TO AGREEMENT ON SENSITIVE INFORMATION & REDACTIONS. NO FOIA WAIVER. STATE-SCB0045106V/r,\r\n\r\nCurrentUser\r\n\r\nCONFIDENTIALITY NOTICE: This e-mail message, including any attachments, may contain information that is protected by the DoD Privacy Act. This e-mail transmission is intended solely for the addressee(s). If you are not the intended recipient, you are hereby notified that you are not authorized to read, print, retain, copy, disclose, distribute, or use this message, any part of it, or any attachments. If you have received this message in error, please immediately notify the sender by telephone or return e-mail and delete this message and any attachments from your system without reading or saving in any manner. You can obtain additional information about the DoD Privacy Act at http://dpclo.defense.gov/privacy.\r\n\r\nTimestamp: Wednesday, 11 March 2026\r\nID: 2ae9bfaf-d0a4-4f92-8cdd-9e1f5d2c3c59","Attachments":[],"BodyType":0}...
