11/03/2026 12:54:44 PM|Trace|Ghosts.Client.Handlers.OutlookHelper.Execute|Built email configuration from timeline {"Id":"12e7f7ef-062e-461f-b8e7-ae6d96b69665","From":"CurrentUser","To":["Hailey.Brazel.mil@mail.mil"],"Cc":[],"Bcc":["Stephani.Harrison.civ@mail.mil","Reginia.Basnight@generaldynamics.com"],"Subject":"\": IT WORKED. SID\"","Body":": It worked. Sid Attachments: hrc memo ni tactic 020810.docx CONFIDENTIAL February 8, 2017 For:  \r\n\r\nFrom: Sid Re: NI/tactic works The plan worked perfectly. Gordon made the speech in the late afternoon. Cameron felt compelled to support both the deal and the timing. Shaun called Lou Susman beforehand and Susman made a helpful call to Cameron \"seeking clarification\" an hour and a half before the event. Now, Reg Empey is boxed in. He's considering his position. It may be that you will have to call him in a couple days. Shaun will call you tomorrow at a time convenient to you.V/r,\r\n\r\nCurrentUser\r\n\r\nCONFIDENTIALITY NOTICE: This e-mail message, including any attachments, may contain information that is protected by the DoD Privacy Act. This e-mail transmission is intended solely for the addressee(s). If you are not the intended recipient, you are hereby notified that you are not authorized to read, print, retain, copy, disclose, distribute, or use this message, any part of it, or any attachments. If you have received this message in error, please immediately notify the sender by telephone or return e-mail and delete this message and any attachments from your system without reading or saving in any manner. You can obtain additional information about the DoD Privacy Act at http://dpclo.defense.gov/privacy.\r\n\r\nTimestamp: Wednesday, 11 March 2026\r\nID: 12e7f7ef-062e-461f-b8e7-ae6d96b69665","Attachments":[],"BodyType":0}...
