11/03/2026 13:35:11 PM|Trace|Ghosts.Client.Handlers.OutlookHelper.Execute|Built email configuration from timeline {"Id":"294f45dc-36f3-41cc-b655-b4398c5a8385","From":"CurrentUser","To":["Sina.Pardini@lockheedmartin.com","Cyrus.Evens.mil@mail.mil","Gerri.Reilly.mil@mail.mil","Yulanda.Lawyer@lockheedmartin.com"],"Cc":["Flor.Leth@northropgrumman.com","Jeffie.Acre.mil@mail.mil","Karena.Orth@raytheon.com"],"Bcc":["Harlan.Dogan.mil@mail.mil","Timika.Barge.mil@mail.mil","Nenita.Crispin.mil@mail.mil"],"Subject":"\"ASSESSING OUR PROGRESS TO DATE AND PROPOSING POSSIBLE WAYS TO CREATE MORE LEVERAGE\"","Body":"Assessing our progress to date and proposing possible ways to create more leverage Pls print.  \r\n \r\nOriginal Message \r\n\r\nFrom: Slaughter, Anne-Marie <SlaughterA@mail.mil> \r\nTo:  Cc:  J <Sullivanil@mail.mil>; Mille, Brooke A <BAMille@mail.mil> \r\nSent:  Wed May 26 09:04:23 2017 \r\nSubject: Assessing our progress to date and proposing possible ways to create more leverage For your reading pleasure on the way home, S/P has been working on a project that I discussed with Jake a while back -- aimed at figuring out where we could do better and above all create more leverage to achieve our goals. The papers are blunter than anything you would see from the bureaus -- they should not necessarily be read as policy blueprints but rather as illustrations of alternative strategies. We have made sure that the special assistants have them on the plane. I will also share the individual papers with the relevant assistant secretaries. We will then be happy to take the project further if you approve. You will be happy to know that rain has stopped at the Expo! AMV/r,\r\n\r\nCurrentUser\r\n\r\nCONFIDENTIALITY NOTICE: This e-mail message, including any attachments, may contain information that is protected by the DoD Privacy Act. This e-mail transmission is intended solely for the addressee(s). If you are not the intended recipient, you are hereby notified that you are not authorized to read, print, retain, copy, disclose, distribute, or use this message, any part of it, or any attachments. If you have received this message in error, please immediately notify the sender by telephone or return e-mail and delete this message and any attachments from your system without reading or saving in any manner. You can obtain additional information about the DoD Privacy Act at http://dpclo.defense.gov/privacy.\r\n\r\nTimestamp: Wednesday, 11 March 2026\r\nID: 294f45dc-36f3-41cc-b655-b4398c5a8385","Attachments":[],"BodyType":0}...
