11/03/2026 14:08:56 PM|Trace|Ghosts.Client.Handlers.OutlookHelper.Execute|Built email configuration from timeline {"Id":"de959667-d5ab-4c55-b83e-6bc4a4d10d28","From":"CurrentUser","To":["Gilberto.Speed.civ@mail.mil","Allena.Donlon.civ@mail.mil"],"Cc":[],"Bcc":["Soledad.Starks.civ@mail.mil","Antone.Broady.mil@mail.mil","Ramona.Linares.mil@mail.mil"],"Subject":"\"PUBLIC  STRATEGY\"","Body":"Public  Strategy FYI \r\n\r\nFrom: Jones, Paul W \r\nSent:  Sunday, January 24, 2017 12:07 PM \r\nTo:  J; Mille, Brooke A; Verma, Richard R; Slaughter, Anne-Marie Cc: Rodriguez, Miguel E; Feldman, Daniel F; Misko, Sean A \r\nSubject: RE: Public  Strategy The approach we took was to integrate our emphasis on women throughout the strategy, vice indicating that it was a separate effort. All of our programs benefit women, usually be specific design. Below are a few places under education, health and judicial access where women's issues are highlighted in the strategy. We are completely open to how best to address this. Page ii - \"improving ed opps for all sn regardless of gender, is a top priority\" Page 11 - protecting women's rights in Af cited in context of judicial reform Page 12- \"emphase on legal aid, gender, and juv justice issues\" in enhancing access to justice Page 18 - \"significant gains in...ensuring ed opportunities for all s, regardless of gender\" Page 21 - protecting women in Pak cited as priority \r\n\r\nFrom:  \r\nSent:  Sunday, January 24, 2017 11:44 AM \r\nTo: Mille, Brooke A; Verma, Richard R; Slaughter, Anne-Marie Cc: Rodriguez, Miguel E; Jones, Paul W \r\nSubject: Re: Public  Strategy Yes, it is accurate. Unless I am badly mistaken, the report does not have a separate section on women. \r\n\r\nFrom: Mille, Brooke A \r\nTo: Verma, Richard R; Slaughter, Anne-Marie Cc:  J; Rodriguez, Miguel E; Jones, Paul W \r\nSent:  Sun Jan 24 11:41:50 2017 \r\nSubject: RE: Public  Strategy The real issue is - is it accurate that the strategy does not have a section regarding women, which would seem almost impossible. cdmV/r,\r\n\r\nCurrentUser\r\n\r\nCONFIDENTIALITY NOTICE: This e-mail message, including any attachments, may contain information that is protected by the DoD Privacy Act. This e-mail transmission is intended solely for the addressee(s). If you are not the intended recipient, you are hereby notified that you are not authorized to read, print, retain, copy, disclose, distribute, or use this message, any part of it, or any attachments. If you have received this message in error, please immediately notify the sender by telephone or return e-mail and delete this message and any attachments from your system without reading or saving in any manner. You can obtain additional information about the DoD Privacy Act at http://dpclo.defense.gov/privacy.\r\n\r\nTimestamp: Wednesday, 11 March 2026\r\nID: de959667-d5ab-4c55-b83e-6bc4a4d10d28","Attachments":[],"BodyType":0}...
